ent-go interface fields\n  Line 383: - [ ] Add K8s client initialization using client-go\n  Line 598: **Verifiable Output:** Session manager works with generated client-go\n  Line 704: - [ ] Compatible with AR-003 (client-go)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/design.md:\n  Line 10: The Router Session Management component provides comprehensive session lifecycle management for the AgentCube Router. It serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n  Line 16: 4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n  Line 136: ├── k8s_client.go               # Kubernetes client-go wrapper\n  Line 323: // RuntimeClient provides typed access to runtime CRDs via client-go.\n  Line 815: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client for runtime CRDs |\n  Line 817: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API client |\n  Line 825: The RuntimeClient uses the generated client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`:\n  Line 829:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n  Line 830:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n  Line 1032: - [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n  Line 1035: - [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go) — Official Go client\n  Line 1036: - [client-go informers](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/informers) — Caching and watching resources\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 9: **Base Spec: